{"TopicId":215859,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"At what altitude around kerbin does the game decide that craft or debris on rails should be removed?","CreatedByName":"Kurld","CreatedById":79950,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T20:05:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kurld","CreatedById":79950,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-24T20:05:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you play the game very long you will see it:\u00A0 decoupled boosters or other garbage in map view that dips well into kerbin\u0027s atmosphere only to emerge on the other side unscathed, and since they are on rails, their orbits never decay and they don\u0027t go away until you bother to go into the tracking station and remove them manually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow low can you go and remain safe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-25T14:20:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265042\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679688307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279950\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kurld\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Kurld said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you play the game very long you will see it:\u00A0 decoupled boosters or other garbage in map view that dips well into kerbin\u0027s atmosphere only to emerge on the other side unscathed, and since they are on rails, their orbits never decay and they don\u0027t go away until you bother to go into the tracking station and remove them manually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow low can you go and remain safe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\niirc, it should be 25 km, as long as you\u0027re not in physical range\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-25T19:10:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLitter bug!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is one of my mission parameters that all debris deorbits itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Leganeski","CreatedById":220954,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-25T20:56:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221679754025\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\niirc, it should be 25 km, as long as you\u0027re not in physical range\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn general I think it\u2019s 0.01 atm, which on Kerbin is at an altitude of about 23 km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kurld","CreatedById":79950,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-26T10:39:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224265480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022215859\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u002216